Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Red paint. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '70'. Name Damophilos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0340.20.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (130)
